title: HENNESSEY -- Harvey Blair Returns ( First Season )
description:
This well-done military series set on a peacetime San Diego naval base was a popular series in 1959 and the early 1960s, and a highlight in the long careers of Jackie Cooper and Abby Dalton.  "Hennessey" arguably started the comedy-drama genre on TV. There was sometimes location shooting in San Diego, but other times it was obvious the navy yard backgrounds were unconvincing stock film footage.

It's kind of rare though not yet on DVD, so I don't have that many episodes. The ones I do have are all supposedly in the public domain.

Before James Komack became a TV producer / director he was a full-time actor, and in this series he had a recurring role in no less than 16 episodes as base dentist Lt. Harvey Spencer Blair.  This is Blair's second appearance
